  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave this message to Hosea son of
        Beeri during the years when Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah were kings
        of Judah, and Jeroboam son of Jehoash[COMMENT[0]] was king of Israel.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Joash, '
        - ft: a variant spelling of Jehoash.
          body: 
    - title: "Hosea\u2019s Wife and Children"
      content: "When the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> first began speaking to Israel
        through Hosea, he said to him, \u201CGo and marry a prostitute,[COMMENT[0]]
        so that some of her children will be conceived in prostitution. This will
        illustrate how Israel has acted like a prostitute by turning against the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and worshiping other gods.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: a promiscuous woman.
    - title: 
      content: 'So Hosea married Gomer, the daughter of Diblaim, and she became pregnant
        and gave Hosea a son. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CName the child Jezreel,
        for I am about to punish King Jehu\u2019s dynasty to avenge the murders he
        committed at Jezreel. In fact, I will bring an end to Israel\u2019s independence. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will break its military power in the Jezreel Valley.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Soon Gomer became pregnant again and gave birth to a daughter. And
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Hosea, \u201CName your daughter Lo-ruhamah\u2014\u2018Not
        loved\u2019\u2014for I will no longer show love to the people of Israel or
        forgive them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I will show love to the people of Judah. I will free them from
        their enemies\u2014not with weapons and armies or horses and charioteers,
        but by my power as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'After Gomer had weaned Lo-ruhamah, she again became pregnant and
        gave birth to a second son. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CName him Lo-ammi\u2014\u2018Not
        my people\u2019\u2014for Israel is not my people, and I am not their God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  [COMMENT[1]]\u201CYet the time will come when Israel\u2019s people
        will be like the sands of the seashore\u2014too many to count! Then, at the
        place where they were told, \u2018You are not my people,\u2019 it will be
        said, \u2018You are children of the living God.\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '1:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
        - ft: Verses 1:10-11 are numbered 2:1-2 in Hebrew text.
          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Then the people of Judah and Israel will unite together. They will
        choose one leader for themselves, and they will return from exile together.
        What a day that will be\u2014the day of Jezreel[COMMENT[0]]\u2014when God
        will again plant his people in his land."
      comments:
      - number: '1:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Jezreel '
        - ft: "means \u201CGod plants.\u201D"
          body: 
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  [COMMENT[1]]\u201CIn that day you will call your brothers Ammi\u2014\u2018My
        people.\u2019 And you will call your sisters Ruhamah\u2014\u2018The ones
        I love.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
