    - title: Charges against an Unfaithful Wife
      content: "\u201CBut now bring charges against Israel\u2014your mother\u2014\n\tfor
        she is no longer my wife,\n\tand I am no longer her husband.\n\tTell her
        to remove the prostitute\u2019s makeup from her face\n\tand the clothing
        that exposes her breasts.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Otherwise, I will strip her as naked\n\tas she was on the day she
        was born.\n\tI will leave her to die of thirst,\n\tas in a dry and barren
        wilderness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I will not love her children,\n\tfor they were conceived in prostitution.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their mother is a shameless prostitute\n\tand became pregnant in
        a shameful way.\n\tShe said, \u2018I\u2019ll run after other lovers\n\tand
        sell myself to them for food and water,\n\tfor clothing of wool and linen,\n\tand
        for olive oil and drinks.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFor this reason I will fence her in with thornbushes.\n\tI
        will block her path with a wall\n\tto make her lose her way.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When she runs after her lovers,\n\tshe won\u2019t be able to catch
        them.\n\tShe will search for them\n\tbut not find them.\n\tThen she will
        think,\n\t\u2018I might as well return to my husband,\n\tfor I was better
        off with him than I am now.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She doesn\u2019t realize it was I who gave her everything she has\u2014\n\tthe
        grain, the new wine, the olive oil;\n\tI even gave her silver and gold.\n\tBut
        she gave all my gifts to Baal.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut now I will take back the ripened grain and new wine\n\tI
        generously provided each harvest season.\n\tI will take away the wool and
        linen clothing\n\tI gave her to cover her nakedness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will strip her naked in public,\n\twhile all her lovers look on.\n\tNo
        one will be able\n\tto rescue her from my hands.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will put an end to her annual festivals,\n\ther new moon celebrations,
        and her Sabbath days\u2014\n\tall her appointed festivals.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will destroy her grapevines and fig trees,\n\tthings she claims
        her lovers gave her.\n\tI will let them grow into tangled thickets,\n\twhere
        only wild animals will eat the fruit.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will punish her for all those times\n\twhen she burned incense
        to her images of Baal,\n\twhen she put on her earrings and jewels\n\tand
        went out to look for her lovers\n\tbut forgot all about me,\u201D\n\tsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "\u2019s Love for Unfaithful Israel"
      content: "\u201CBut then I will win her back once again.\n\tI will lead her
        into the desert\n\tand speak tenderly to her there.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will return her vineyards to her\n\tand transform the Valley of
        Trouble[COMMENT[0]] into a gateway of hope.\n\tShe will give herself to me
        there,\n\tas she did long ago when she was young,\n\twhen I freed her from
        her captivity in Egypt.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: valley of Achor.
    - title: 
      content: "When that day comes,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201Cyou
        will call me \u2018my husband\u2019\n\tinstead of \u2018my master.\u2019[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:16 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: "\u2018my baal.\u2019"
    - title: 
      content: "O Israel, I will wipe the many names of Baal from your lips,\n\tand
        you will never mention them again.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "On that day I will make a covenant\n\twith all the wild animals and
        the birds of the sky\n\tand the animals that scurry along the ground\n\tso
        they will not harm you.\n\tI will remove all weapons of war from the land,\n\tall
        swords and bows,\n\tso you can live unafraid\n\tin peace and safety.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will make you my wife forever,\n\tshowing you righteousness and
        justice,\n\tunfailing love and compassion.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will be faithful to you and make you mine,\n\tand you will finally
        know me as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn that day, I will answer,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CI
        will answer the sky as it pleads for clouds.\n\tAnd the sky will answer the
        earth with rain.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the earth will answer the thirsty cries\n\tof the grain, the
        grapevines, and the olive trees.\n\tAnd they in turn will answer,\n\t\u2018Jezreel\u2019\u2014\u2018God
        plants!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At that time I will plant a crop of Israelites\n\tand raise them
        for myself.\n\tI will show love\n\tto those I called \u2018Not loved.\u2019[COMMENT[0]]And
        to those I called \u2018Not my people,\u2019[COMMENT[1]]I will say, \u2018Now
        you are my people.\u2019\n\tAnd they will reply, \u2018You are our God!\u2019\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '2:23a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Lo-ruhamah; '
        - ft: see 1:6.
          body: 
      - number: '2:23b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Lo-ammi; '
        - ft: see 1:9.
          body: 
  - verses:
    - title: "Hosea\u2019s Wife Is Redeemed"
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CGo and love
        your wife again, even though she[COMMENT[0]] commits adultery with another
        lover. This will illustrate that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> still loves
        Israel, even though the people have turned to other gods and love to worship
        them.[COMMENT[1]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:1a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Go and love a woman who.
      - number: '3:1b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: love their raisin cakes.
    - title: 
      content: 'So I bought her back for fifteen pieces of silver[COMMENT[0]] and
        five bushels of barley and a measure of wine.[COMMENT[1]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:2a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: '15 [shekels] of silver, '
        - ft: about 6 ounces or 171 grams in weight.
          body: 
      - number: '3:2b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek version, which reads '
          body: 'a homer of barley and a wineskin full of wine; '
        - ft: 'Hebrew reads '
          body: 'a homer '
        - ft: '[5 bushels or 220 liters] '
          body: 'of barley and a lethek '
        - ft: '[2.5 bushels or 110 liters] '
          body: of barley.
    - title: 
      content: "Then I said to her, \u201CYou must live in my house for many days
        and stop your prostitution. During this time, you will not have sexual relations
        with anyone, not even with me.[COMMENT[0]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: and I will live with you.
    - title: 
      content: 'This shows that Israel will go a long time without a king or prince,
        and without sacrifices, sacred pillars, priests,[COMMENT[0]] or even idols! '
      comments:
      - number: '3:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'ephod, '
        - ft: the vest worn by the priest.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "But afterward the people will return and devote themselves to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God and to David\u2019s descendant, their
        king.[COMMENT[0]] In the last days, they will tremble in awe of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and of his goodness."
      comments:
      - number: '3:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: to David their king.
  - verses:
    - title: "\u2019s Case against Israel"
      content: "Hear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, O people of
        Israel!\n\tThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has brought charges against you,
        saying:\n\t\u201CThere is no faithfulness, no kindness,\n\tno knowledge of
        God in your land.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You make vows and break them;\n\tyou kill and steal and commit adultery.\n\tThere
        is violence everywhere\u2014\n\tone murder after another.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That is why your land is in mourning,\n\tand everyone is wasting
        away.\n\tEven the wild animals, the birds of the sky,\n\tand the fish of
        the sea are disappearing.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDon\u2019t point your finger at someone else\n\tand try to
        pass the blame!\n\tMy complaint, you priests,\n\tis with you.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Your people are like those with a complaint against the priests.
    - title: 
      content: "So you will stumble in broad daylight,\n\tand your false prophets
        will fall with you in the night.\n\tAnd I will destroy Israel, your mother.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My people are being destroyed\n\tbecause they don\u2019t know me.\n\tSince
        you priests refuse to know me,\n\tI refuse to recognize you as my priests.\n\tSince
        you have forgotten the laws of your God,\n\tI will forget to bless your children.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The more priests there are,\n\tthe more they sin against me.\n\tThey
        have exchanged the glory of God\n\tfor the shame of idols.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Syriac version and an ancient Hebrew tradition; Masoretic Text
            reads '
          body: I will turn their glory into shame.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen the people bring their sin offerings, the priests get
        fed.\n\tSo the priests are glad when the people sin!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018And what the priests do, the people also do.\u2019\n\tSo now
        I will punish both priests and people\n\tfor their wicked deeds.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will eat and still be hungry.\n\tThey will play the prostitute
        and gain nothing from it,\n\tfor they have deserted the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "to worship other gods.\n\t\u201CWine has robbed my people\n\tof their
        understanding.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They ask a piece of wood for advice!\n\tThey think a stick can tell
        them the future!\n\tLonging after idols\n\thas made them foolish.\n\tThey
        have played the prostitute,\n\tserving other gods and deserting their God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They offer sacrifices to idols on the mountaintops.\n\tThey go up
        into the hills to burn incense\n\tin the pleasant shade of oaks, poplars,
        and terebinth trees.\n\t\u201CThat is why your daughters turn to prostitution,\n\tand
        your daughters-in-law commit adultery.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But why should I punish them\n\tfor their prostitution and adultery?\n\tFor
        your men are doing the same thing,\n\tsinning with whores and shrine prostitutes.\n\tO
        foolish people! You refuse to understand,\n\tso you will be destroyed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThough you, Israel, are a prostitute,\n\tmay Judah not be guilty
        of such things.\n\tDo not join the false worship at Gilgal or Beth-aven,[COMMENT[0]]and
        do not take oaths there in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s name.  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Beth-aven '
        - ft: "means \u201Chouse of wickedness\u201D; it is being used as another
            name for Bethel, which means \u201Chouse of God.\u201D"
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Israel is stubborn,\n\tlike a stubborn heifer.\n\tSo should the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        feed her\n\tlike a lamb in a lush pasture?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Leave Israel[COMMENT[0]] alone,\n\tbecause she is married to idolatry.  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:17 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Ephraim, '
        - ft: referring to the northern kingdom of Israel.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "When the rulers of Israel finish their drinking,\n\toff they go to
        find some prostitutes.\n\tThey love shame more than honor.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: As in Greek version; the meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "So a mighty wind will sweep them away.\n\tTheir sacrifices to idols
        will bring them shame."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "The Failure of Israel\u2019s Leaders"
      content: "\u201CHear this, you priests.\n\tPay attention, you leaders of Israel.\n\tListen,
        you members of the royal family.\n\tJudgment has been handed down against
        you.\n\tFor you have led the people into a snare\n\tby worshiping the idols
        at Mizpah and Tabor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have dug a deep pit to trap them at Acacia Grove.[COMMENT[0]]But
        I will settle with you for what you have done.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'at Shittim. '
        - ft: The meaning of the Hebrew for this sentence is uncertain.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "I know what you are like, O Ephraim.\n\tYou cannot hide yourself
        from me, O Israel.\n\tYou have left me as a prostitute leaves her husband;\n\tyou
        are utterly defiled.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your deeds won\u2019t let you return to your God.\n\tYou are a prostitute
        through and through,\n\tand you do not know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe arrogance of Israel testifies against her;\n\tIsrael and
        Ephraim will stumble under their load of guilt.\n\tJudah, too, will fall
        with them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When they come with their flocks and herds\n\tto offer sacrifices
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tthey will not find him,\n\tbecause
        he has withdrawn from them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They have betrayed the honor of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tbearing
        children that are not his.\n\tNow their false religion will devour them\n\talong
        with their wealth.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSound the alarm in Gibeah!\n\tBlow the trumpet in Ramah!\n\tRaise
        the battle cry in Beth-aven[COMMENT[0]]!\n\tLead on into battle, O warriors
        of Benjamin!  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Beth-aven '
        - ft: "means \u201Chouse of wickedness\u201D; it is being used as another
            name for Bethel, which means \u201Chouse of God.\u201D"
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "One thing is certain, Israel[COMMENT[0]]:\n\tOn your day of punishment,\n\tyou
        will become a heap of rubble.  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Ephraim, '
        - ft: referring to the northern kingdom of Israel; also in 5:11, 12, 13,
            14.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe leaders of Judah have become like thieves.[COMMENT[0]]So
        I will pour my anger on them like a waterfall.  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: like those who move a boundary marker.
    - title: 
      content: "The people of Israel will be crushed and broken by my judgment\n\tbecause
        they are determined to worship idols.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'determined to follow human commands. '
        - ft: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "I will destroy Israel as a moth consumes wool.\n\tI will make Judah
        as weak as rotten wood.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen Israel and Judah saw how sick they were,\n\tIsrael turned
        to Assyria\u2014\n\tto the great king there\u2014\n\tbut he could neither
        help nor cure them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will be like a lion to Israel,\n\tlike a strong young lion to Judah.\n\tI
        will tear them to pieces!\n\tI will carry them off,\n\tand no one will be
        left to rescue them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I will return to my place\n\tuntil they admit their guilt and
        turn to me.\n\tFor as soon as trouble comes,\n\tthey will earnestly search
        for me.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Call to Repentance
      content: "\u201CCome, let us return to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tHe
        has torn us to pieces;\n\tnow he will heal us.\n\tHe has injured us;\n\tnow
        he will bandage our wounds.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In just a short time he will restore us,\n\tso that we may live in
        his presence.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Oh, that we might know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t!\n\tLet
        us press on to know him.\n\tHe will respond to us as surely as the arrival
        of dawn\n\tor the coming of rains in early spring.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO Israel[COMMENT[0]] and Judah,\n\twhat should I do with you?\u201D
        asks the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CFor your love vanishes
        like the morning mist\n\tand disappears like dew in the sunlight.  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Ephraim, '
        - ft: referring to the northern kingdom of Israel.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "I sent my prophets to cut you to pieces\u2014\n\tto slaughter you
        with my words,\n\twith judgments as inescapable as light.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I want you to show love,[COMMENT[0]]not offer sacrifices.\n\tI want
        you to know me[COMMENT[1]]more than I want burnt offerings.  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:6a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version translates this Hebrew term as '
          body: 'to show mercy. '
        - ft: Compare Matt 9:13; 12:7.
          body: 
      - number: '6:6b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: to know God.
    - title: 
      content: "But like Adam,[COMMENT[0]] you broke my covenant\n\tand betrayed
        my trust.  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: But at Adam.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGilead is a city of sinners,\n\ttracked with footprints of
        blood.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Priests form bands of robbers,\n\twaiting in ambush for their victims.\n\tThey
        murder travelers along the road to Shechem\n\tand practice every kind of
        sin.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
