        in the morning sun,\n\tlike chaff blown by the wind,\n\tlike smoke from a
        chimney.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI have been the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God\n\tever
        since I brought you out of Egypt.\n\tYou must acknowledge no God but me,\n\tfor
        there is no other savior.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I took care of you in the wilderness,\n\tin that dry and thirsty
        land.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But when you had eaten and were satisfied,\n\tyou became proud and
        forgot me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So now I will attack you like a lion,\n\tlike a leopard that lurks
        along the road.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Like a bear whose cubs have been taken away,\n\tI will tear out your
        heart.\n\tI will devour you like a hungry lioness\n\tand mangle you like
        a wild animal.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou are about to be destroyed, O Israel\u2014\n\tyes, by me,
        your only helper.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now where is[COMMENT[0]] your king?\n\tLet him save you!\n\tWhere
